, England"},"en":{"1520–1591":"1520–1591","1515–1591":"1515–1591","1535–1578":"1535–1578","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1535":"1535","1578":"1578","1587":"1587","1520":"1520","1585":"1585","1591":"1591","1549":"1549","1515":"1515","Haverhill, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Haverhill, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","York, Yorkshire, England":"York, Yorkshire, England","Mappleton, Yorkshire, England":"Mappleton, Yorkshire, England","Withersfield, Suffolk, England":"Withersfield, Suffolk, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Milborne","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English:  see  Milburn  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Milburn","meanings":["English (Northumberland, Cumberland and Durham): habitational name from any of the places in Westmorland, Northumberland, Somerset, Dorset or Wiltshire, all derived from Old English <i>myln</i> ‘mill’ + <i>burna</i> ‘spring, stream’. There has been some confusion with   Melbourne  ."]}]},{"name":"Mary","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Hebrew: Bitter; Marion is the French form."],"variants":[{"name":"Marion","meanings":["Originally a medieval French diminutive form of   Marie  , introduced to Britain in the Middle Ages. In some places it was taken as a pet form of   Margaret   or   Margery .  As a male name, it is an altered form of the Continental male name <i>Marian</i>, a derivative of Latin <i>Marianus</i> (from   Marius  ), but is now rarely, if ever, used. It was the birth name of the American film star  John Wayne  (  1907–79 )."]},{"name":"Marcia","meanings":["Often used as a feminine equivalent of   Mark  , but in fact a feminine form of <i>Marcius</i>, itself a derivative of   Marcus .  One  St Marcia  is commemorated in a group with Felix, Luciolus, Fortunatus, and others; another with Zenais, Cyria, and Valeria; and a third with Ariston, Crescentian, Eutychian, Urban, Vitalis, Justus, Felicissimus, Felix, and Symphorosa. None is individually very famous."]}]},{"name":"Ann","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Anne .  In the U.S. <i>Ann</i> is the more frequent spelling."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705201,"age":29,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705202,"age":38,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705205,"age":49,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705207,"age":65,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705208,"age":67,"year":"1587","julianDay":2300700,"title":"Elizabeth I Signs Death Warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots","description":"Elizabeth I signed the death warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots, on February 1, 1587, as she was found guilty of plotting to assasinate Elizabeth. Mary, Queen of Scots, was beheaded at Fotheringhay Castle in England on February 8, 1587.","url":"https://www.elizabethi.org/mary_queen_of_scots/","urlTitle":"Elizabeth I.org - Mary Queen of Scots","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Mary Ann Milborne was born in 1520, in Withersfield, Suffolk, England. She had at least 1 daughter with Sir William John Marsh. She died in 1591, in Haverhill, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 71."},"et":{"1520–1591":"1520–1591","1515–1591":"1515–1591","1535–1578":"1535–1578","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1535":"1535","1578":"1578","1587":"1587","1520":"1520","1585":"1585","1591":"1591","1549":"1549","1515":"1515","Haverhill, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Haverhill, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","York, Yorkshire, England":"York, Yorkshire, England","Mappleton, Yorkshire, England":"Mappleton, Yorkshire, England","Withersfield, Suffolk, England":"Withersfield, Suffolk, England"},"fi":{"1520–1591":"1520–1591","1515–1591":"1515–1591","1535–1578":"1535–1578","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1535":"1535","1578":"1578","1587":"1587","1520":"1520","1585":"1585","1591":"1591","1549":"1549","1515":"1515","Haverhill, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Haverhill, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","York, Yorkshire, England":"York, Yorkshire, England","Mappleton, Yorkshire, England":"Mappleton, Yorkshire, England","Withersfield, Suffolk, England":"Withersfield, Suffolk, England"},"fr":{"1520–1591":"1520–1591","1515–1591":"1515–1591","1535–1578":"1535–1578","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1535":"1535","1578":"1578","1587":"1587","1520":"1520","1585":"1585","1591":"1591","1549":"1549","1515":"1515","Haverhill, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Haverhill, Suffolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","York, Yorkshire, England":"York, Everwyck, Angleterre","Mappleton, Yorkshire, England":"Mappleton, Everwyck, Angleterre","Withersfield, Suffolk, England":"Withers